.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH my-app 1  "my-app 1.0" 
.SH NAME
my\-app \- A \fBbold\fR and \fIitalic\fR app with \fBcode\fR
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmy\-app\fR [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIinput\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
This is a tool for testing \fBmarkdown\fR rendering.
.SS Features
.IP \(bu 2
Supports \fBbold\fR text
.IP \(bu 2
Supports \fIitalic\fR text
.IP \(bu 2
Supports \fBcode\fR spans
.SS Examples
.nf
my\-app \-\-flag value

.fi
For more info see the docs <https://example.com>.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-format\fR
Output \fBformat\fR to use
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
[\fIinput\fR]
The \fIinput\fR file to process (use \fBstdin\fR for \fBstandard input\fR)
.SH EXTRA
.SS Notes
.RS 4
This is a blockquote with \fBbold\fR text.
.RE
.IP 1. 4
First step
.IP 2. 4
Second step
.IP 3. 4
Third step
.SH VERSION
v1.0
